data.title: Musicians Born in 1849
data.meta_description: Birthdays in music in 1849. See which composers, musicians, pop stars and rockers were born in 1849 or search by date or keyword.
data.text:
"Blind" Tom Wiggins, African-American pianist and composer, born in Harris County, Georgia (d. 1908) [1] [2]

Joseph Vézina, Québécois conductor, composer, organist, and music professor, born in Quebec City, British Province of Canada (d. 1924)

Moritz Heuzenroeder, German pianist and composer who settled in Australia, born in Ottersberg, Kingdom of Hanover (d. 1897)

Géza Zichy, Hungarian composer and one-armed pianist, born at Sztára Castle, Hungary (d. 1924)

Benjamin Godard, French violinist, orchestral and opera composer (Symphonie légendaire; Jocelyn), born in Paris, France (d. 1895)

Vaclav Juda Novotny, Czech composer and music critic, born in Vesce (d. 1922)

Mikhail Ivanov, Russian composer, born in Moscow, Russia (d. 1927)

Ladislao Zavertal, Czech-Italian conductor and composer, born in Milan, Italy (d. 1942)

Arnold Krug, German composer, born in Hamburg, German Confederation (now Germany) (d. 1904)

Oct 16 Charles Harford Lloyd, British organist and composer, born in Thornbury, Gloucestershire, England (d. 1919)

Edward Julius Biedermann, American organist and composer, born in Milwaukee, Wisconsin (d. 1933)
